    "elements": [
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-s00348-006-0117-x.pdf_11_4",
        "observed_type": "section_header",
        "canon_role": "section_header",
        "text": "2.10 Identification of vortex parameters",
        "bbox": [
          0.08045977473983947,
          0.5014534881645708,
          0.3773946315341069,
          0.5146329365534423
        ],
        "order": 39
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-s00348-006-0117-x.pdf_11_42",
        "observed_type": "caption",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Fig. 10 Elimination of disturbing structures. BL, pos. 47 of Fig. 1, simple average",
        "bbox": [
          0.5076294319764507,
          0.5203373014597316,
          0.9195402144499726,
          0.5437613043338683
        ],
        "order": 40
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-s00348-006-0117-x.pdf_11_5",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The identification of the swirl and the axial velocity profiles, the core radius and the circulation is often hindered by other flow structures in close proximity of the vortex of interest. These are shear layers with vorticity and additional vortices shed by other blades just passing the measurement window, especially where BVI takes place.",
        "bbox": [
          0.08029507252940708,
          0.5281059249730957,
          0.492337163045119,
          0.6308798277997147
        ],
        "order": 41
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-s00348-006-0117-x.pdf_11_43",
