        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Vatistas model is used here, since with the shape parameter n a wide range of swirl shapes can be defined, covering the Scully vortex (n=1), the Lamb Oseen vortex (n~2), or the Rankine vortex (n=∞). When the data are cleaned from spurious vectors, mean values of the flow subtracted and rotated into the vortex axis system, the distribution of swirl velocities of all vectors is fitted with the Vatistas model using a least squares error method. The best fit is performed at a radial extension of 2-3 core radii.",
